WEBVTT

00:04.003 --> 00:04.879
DANIEL: Uh...

00:04.963 --> 00:05.755
- What are you doing here?

00:05.839 --> 00:08.675
- I just came by
to come see you,

00:08.758 --> 00:11.052
and the door was open,
so I just walked in...

00:13.179 --> 00:14.431
And I'm just so used
to coming in through

00:14.514 --> 00:15.765
the back door here
without knocking.

00:15.849 --> 00:17.392
- [mouths words]

00:17.475 --> 00:19.769
- Okay, I'm good with that,
but we're on the second floor.

00:19.853 --> 00:21.104
Are you okay
with climbing down?

00:21.187 --> 00:22.147
- Like old times?

00:22.230 --> 00:23.022
- Yeah, I guess.

00:24.399 --> 00:26.109
- "Like old times"?

00:26.192 --> 00:28.027
- Focus!
Come on.

00:29.821 --> 00:31.448
Shh, shh.
[mouths words]

00:32.866 --> 00:35.076
- I have to tell you,
Daniel, it's creepy,

00:35.160 --> 00:37.996
yet incredibly romantic
to find you here.

00:38.079 --> 00:39.372
- Maddie, I--

00:39.456 --> 00:40.707
- And don't think
it's going to be so easy.

00:40.790 --> 00:43.752
I mean, you just show up,
and, boom, I forgive you.

00:43.835 --> 00:45.879
- No, that's not...

00:45.962 --> 00:46.963
[thud]

00:47.964 --> 00:49.466
- What was that?

00:49.549 --> 00:50.967
- It's probably the wind.

00:51.050 --> 00:52.135
I mean, it's so strong,
it nearly knocked me over.

00:53.595 --> 00:55.638
No, wait a minute.

00:55.722 --> 00:58.641
[hums and stutters]

00:58.725 --> 00:59.768
You want to dance?

01:01.144 --> 01:02.896
- Oh, I get it.

01:02.979 --> 01:04.480
You're upset
because Diego asked me

01:04.563 --> 01:06.399
to the Get Your Anime On dance.

01:06.483 --> 01:09.652
Are you trying to ask me
to go to the dance with you

01:09.736 --> 01:11.488
instead of Diego?

01:11.571 --> 01:12.489
- No!

01:12.572 --> 01:13.656
I mean, um...

01:15.074 --> 01:16.701
- Let me through.
- Wait.

01:18.286 --> 01:18.745
This is for you.

01:18.828 --> 01:21.623
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

01:21.706 --> 01:26.085
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:26.169 --> 01:28.129
{\an8}<i>[upbeat pop music]</i>

01:28.213 --> 01:29.964
{\an8}<i>WOMAN: ♪ I cast a spell ♪</i>

01:30.048 --> 01:31.758
{\an8}<i>♪ It takes a hold of you ♪</i>

01:31.841 --> 01:33.718
{\an8}<i>♪ I see my dreams ♪</i>

01:33.802 --> 01:35.470
{\an8}<i>♪ And they're all</i>
<i>coming true ♪</i>

01:35.553 --> 01:36.471
{\an8}<i>♪ Come on ♪</i>

01:36.554 --> 01:37.430
{\an8}<i>♪ Let's go ♪</i>

01:37.514 --> 01:39.224
{\an8}<i>♪ You and me together ♪</i>

01:39.307 --> 01:40.433
{\an8}<i>♪ Look up ahead ♪</i>

01:40.517 --> 01:42.644
{\an8}<i>♪ There's a magical adventure ♪</i>

01:42.727 --> 01:44.312
{\an8}<i>♪ Every witch way ♪</i>

01:44.395 --> 01:46.022
{\an8}<i>♪ Ay-ay-ay-ay-ay ♪</i>

01:46.105 --> 01:47.941
<i>♪ I'm trying</i>
<i>every witch way ♪</i>

01:48.024 --> 01:49.567
<i>♪ Ay-ay-ay-ay-ay ♪</i>

01:49.651 --> 01:51.694
<i>♪ I'm going</i>
<i>every witch way ♪</i>

01:51.778 --> 01:53.696
<i>♪ Ay-ay-ay-ay-ay ♪</i>

01:53.780 --> 01:54.239
<i>♪ Every witch way ♪</i>

01:56.950 --> 01:57.909
{\an8}- You wrote me a song?

01:57.992 --> 01:58.952
{\an8}- Mm-hmm.

01:59.035 --> 02:00.203
{\an8}- This means so much to me.

02:01.871 --> 02:04.833
- Great, well,
I'm gonna go.

02:04.916 --> 02:07.710
<i>[hip-hop music]</i>

02:07.794 --> 02:08.877
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:08.961 --> 02:10.420
- I'm going to listen to it
right now.

02:10.505 --> 02:12.590
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:12.674 --> 02:13.216
- [sighs]

02:13.299 --> 02:14.551
<i>MAN: ♪ Yeah ♪</i>

02:14.634 --> 02:15.760
[glass cracks]

02:15.844 --> 02:19.556
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:19.639 --> 02:27.689
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:29.649 --> 02:32.610
<i>[eerie music]</i>

02:32.694 --> 02:36.865
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:36.948 --> 02:38.992
DIEGO: Witches and Kanays,

02:39.075 --> 02:41.035
they really don't
like each other.

02:41.119 --> 02:42.245
- That's the principal.

02:42.328 --> 02:42.829
And who's that?

02:42.912 --> 02:44.956
- I can't tell.

02:45.039 --> 02:47.959
It kind of looks like...

02:48.042 --> 02:49.043
Maddie.

02:49.127 --> 02:50.336
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:50.420 --> 02:51.796
- Wait, here's another one.

02:51.880 --> 02:54.132
It's--it's you!

02:54.215 --> 02:56.175
- Quick, see if there are
any more drawings of me.

02:56.259 --> 02:57.135
- Yeah.

02:57.218 --> 03:00.263
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:00.346 --> 03:02.432
- The principal thought
we shredded all the copies,

03:02.515 --> 03:05.226
but I managed
to sneak one out.

03:06.811 --> 03:09.772
I have to find a good hiding
spot for this, just in case.

03:09.856 --> 03:12.233
- In case what?

03:12.317 --> 03:14.110
- Someone tries to steal it.

03:14.193 --> 03:16.905
Somebody was
in my room today.

03:21.951 --> 03:23.161
- You look
just like your father.

03:23.244 --> 03:26.414
- [scoffs]
That's not the point.

03:27.582 --> 03:29.500
This was in my trunk,

03:29.584 --> 03:33.463
my locked trunk.

03:33.546 --> 03:34.464
- It had to be Emma.

03:34.547 --> 03:37.175
- Meaning she was
just in here?

03:37.258 --> 03:39.427
Ugh, and ew!

03:39.510 --> 03:41.971
And the nerve!

03:42.055 --> 03:45.516
- Is your mom
still convinced Emma's poof?

03:46.059 --> 03:47.685
- She might be,

03:47.769 --> 03:49.270
or she might be using it
as an excuse

03:49.354 --> 03:51.022
to cry on
Mr. Alonso's shoulder.

03:51.105 --> 03:52.357
- Anyone could have gotten
into this trunk.

03:52.440 --> 03:54.943
I mean,
who doesn't know how to pick

03:55.026 --> 03:57.487
a cheap lock like this one?

03:57.570 --> 04:00.573
You do look
just like your dad,

04:00.657 --> 04:03.368
very distinguished.

04:04.911 --> 04:08.623
- Do you think Daniel
was just here to distract you

04:08.706 --> 04:12.919
so Emma could sneak in and out?

04:13.002 --> 04:14.003
- No!

04:14.087 --> 04:15.755
And how dare you say that?

04:15.838 --> 04:18.841
<i>[electronic music]</i>

04:18.925 --> 04:22.887
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:22.971 --> 04:25.723
- [whimpering]

04:25.807 --> 04:27.642
- Hi, Em, it's Dad.

04:27.725 --> 04:28.518
Just making sure
you're okay.

04:28.601 --> 04:31.521
- [crying]
She's gone!

04:31.604 --> 04:32.814
Gone!

04:32.897 --> 04:33.564
[sobs]

04:33.648 --> 04:35.066
- I assume you heard that,

04:35.149 --> 04:37.360
so, uh, call me
when you get this, okay?

04:39.445 --> 04:41.114
Oh, Emma.

04:41.197 --> 04:43.116
- [gasps]
Emma!

04:43.199 --> 04:45.159
Oh! Oh! Oh!

04:45.243 --> 04:46.244
<i>[quirky music]</i>

04:46.327 --> 04:47.870
Is she a ghost?

04:47.954 --> 04:49.580
Are you--are you a ghost?

04:49.664 --> 04:51.374
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:51.457 --> 04:52.542
Oh, she's real!

04:52.625 --> 04:53.543
She's real!

04:53.626 --> 04:54.794
She's--

04:54.877 --> 04:56.587
- See, she's fine.

04:56.671 --> 04:58.089
- Yes! Yes!
Yes.

04:58.172 --> 04:59.799
It appears that she is

04:59.882 --> 05:02.760
just fine, yeah.

05:02.844 --> 05:04.137
- Ursula?
- Hmm?

05:04.220 --> 05:05.388
- Are you okay?

05:05.471 --> 05:09.767
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:09.851 --> 05:11.853
- I told you, Katie, no way.

05:11.936 --> 05:13.229
Daniel would never do that.

05:13.312 --> 05:14.313
- But he--

05:14.397 --> 05:15.773
Why was he here then?

05:15.857 --> 05:17.150
- He came to bring me this.

05:18.109 --> 05:20.111
He made me a song.

05:20.194 --> 05:22.739
- Wow, how very
Taylor Swift of him.

05:22.822 --> 05:24.157
- I know!

05:24.240 --> 05:25.033
- You know,
that could go either way,

05:25.116 --> 05:26.409
because there's a sweet,

05:26.492 --> 05:29.245
"we drink lattes
and hold hands together" songs,

05:29.328 --> 05:31.539
and then there's an angry,

05:31.622 --> 05:34.250
"never ever gonna get
back together" songs.

05:34.334 --> 05:35.376
- Well, this is
a lattes and holding hands one.

05:35.460 --> 05:37.045
Do you want to hear it?
- Not really.

05:37.128 --> 05:40.131
- Yes, we'd love to.

05:44.719 --> 05:46.095
<i>DANIEL: ♪ I know</i>
<i>it's been a while ♪</i>

05:46.179 --> 05:49.057
<i>♪ But I got to let you know ♪</i>

05:49.140 --> 05:50.975
- Oh, the one he performed
at The Seven.

05:51.059 --> 05:52.268
- He wrote this for you?

05:52.351 --> 05:55.730
- He wrote, sang it,
and recorded it just for me.

05:55.813 --> 05:57.148
- Are you sure?

05:57.231 --> 05:59.025
It doesn't sound
like a breakup song.

05:59.108 --> 06:00.234
- It's not.

06:00.318 --> 06:02.820
Are you not listening
closely to the lyrics?

06:02.904 --> 06:03.780
<i>DANIEL: ♪ Every</i>
<i>Sunday afternoon ♪</i>

06:03.863 --> 06:07.241
- Now listen.

06:07.325 --> 06:10.286
<i>DANIEL: ♪ Thinking of me</i>
<i>and you ♪</i>

06:10.369 --> 06:12.455
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

06:12.538 --> 06:14.123
- Ooh, a bonus track.

06:14.207 --> 06:16.918
<i>DANIEL: I know we're young,</i>

06:17.001 --> 06:19.170
<i>but I need you</i>
<i>to know how I feel.</i>

06:19.253 --> 06:20.421
- [giggles]

06:20.505 --> 06:22.590
<i>DANIEL: What we've got</i>
<i>between us, Emma,</i>

06:22.673 --> 06:24.217
<i>it's the real deal.</i>

06:24.300 --> 06:25.343
- Emma?

06:25.426 --> 06:26.636
Did he say Emma?

06:28.513 --> 06:29.013
- Quick, grab the drawings.

06:29.097 --> 06:29.972
<i>[eerie music]</i>

06:30.056 --> 06:31.933
- [whispers] I got it.

06:32.016 --> 06:33.351
[thud]

06:33.434 --> 06:34.435
[rattling]

06:34.519 --> 06:35.353
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:35.436 --> 06:36.646
- What was that noise?

06:36.729 --> 06:39.357
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:39.440 --> 06:40.858
- What noise?

06:40.942 --> 06:43.152
- I heard something
coming from the lair.

06:43.236 --> 06:46.072
- So, um, the eclipse...

06:46.155 --> 06:49.158
powers, you.

06:49.242 --> 06:50.993
Are we still using the Kanay
as a conduit?

06:52.912 --> 06:55.123
- That's the plan,

06:55.206 --> 06:58.376
which means I'll have
to hold the Kanay's hand

06:58.459 --> 07:00.837
for a moment
during the transfer of power.

07:01.712 --> 07:04.590
- But wouldn't that, um...

07:04.674 --> 07:06.634
[gags] Diego?

07:06.717 --> 07:08.886
You know, poof.

07:08.970 --> 07:11.180
- I don't know.
Who cares?

07:11.264 --> 07:12.223
- [whispering]
What are they saying?

07:12.306 --> 07:14.559
- I don't know,
but I think I just heard

07:14.642 --> 07:15.268
one of them say "Diego."

07:15.351 --> 07:18.855
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

07:18.938 --> 07:23.693
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:23.776 --> 07:25.278
<i>[rock music]</i>

07:25.361 --> 07:26.404
[doorbell rings]

07:27.905 --> 07:29.615
- Andi, do you need help
carrying that toolbox home?

07:32.034 --> 07:34.704
<i>[tender instrumental music]</i>

07:34.787 --> 07:35.705
- Can we talk?

07:35.788 --> 07:38.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:38.374 --> 07:40.251
- My aquarium's
getting awfully crowded.

07:40.334 --> 07:41.210
[frog croaks]

07:41.294 --> 07:42.211
- Maybe you should

07:42.295 --> 07:43.588
just turn some of them back.

07:43.671 --> 07:44.714
- I will.

07:44.797 --> 07:47.175
But not until
I'm the Chosen One,

07:47.258 --> 07:49.635
and then I'll be able
to change them back

07:49.719 --> 07:51.512
and make them
part of my army.

07:51.596 --> 07:52.638
[frog croaks]

07:53.723 --> 07:56.559
Who's going to be
my lieutenant?

07:56.642 --> 07:57.560
[frog croaks]

07:57.643 --> 08:00.396
Which one of you
has what it takes?

08:00.479 --> 08:03.065
- Are you expecting me
to be in this army?

08:03.149 --> 08:04.317
[frog croaks]

08:04.400 --> 08:05.818
- Of course.

08:05.902 --> 08:07.528
- What if, um,

08:07.612 --> 08:09.655
let's just say...

08:09.739 --> 08:11.616
I didn't want
to be part of that army?

08:11.699 --> 08:13.576
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

08:13.659 --> 08:14.994
What happens then?

08:15.077 --> 08:16.579
TORRES: You go back
to your original form

08:16.662 --> 08:19.123
and have this entire aquarium
to yourself.

08:19.207 --> 08:20.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:20.541 --> 08:22.251
JULIO: Good thing I'll
definitely be loyal to you

08:22.335 --> 08:24.045
during the eclipse.

08:24.128 --> 08:26.589
- And celebrate with me
when the evil Kanay

08:26.672 --> 08:28.549
formerly known as Diego

08:28.633 --> 08:31.260
disintegrates
into a pile of dust?

08:31.344 --> 08:32.428
- Of course.

08:32.510 --> 08:33.429
I'll...

08:33.511 --> 08:35.765
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:35.847 --> 08:37.683
Ah--
- Julio?

08:37.767 --> 08:39.769
- I will celebrate, um,

08:39.852 --> 08:43.147
you becoming
the strongest witch ever.

08:43.231 --> 08:51.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:56.077 --> 08:57.453
- Is something wrong?
- What?

08:57.536 --> 08:57.954
Uh...
[chuckles]

08:58.037 --> 09:00.206
No.

09:00.289 --> 09:02.625
Um, didn't you want
to go check on that--

09:02.708 --> 09:04.460
on that new girl?

09:04.543 --> 09:06.629
- Yes.
- No time like the present.

09:06.712 --> 09:07.588
Let's go.

09:07.672 --> 09:08.047
We have no time to waste.

09:08.130 --> 09:09.966
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:10.049 --> 09:11.384
TORRES: You're right.

09:11.467 --> 09:12.468
We better go.

09:12.551 --> 09:19.600
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:25.398 --> 09:26.649
- Coach Julio, wow.

09:28.567 --> 09:30.361
- I know, and all this time,

09:30.444 --> 09:31.904
I thought he was trying
to help me.

09:32.446 --> 09:34.073
- Sorry, bro,

09:34.156 --> 09:34.782
but let's get out of here

09:34.865 --> 09:35.408
before they come back.

09:35.491 --> 09:38.953
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:39.036 --> 09:39.745
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:39.829 --> 09:42.331
- Thanks for distracting Maddie.

09:42.415 --> 09:44.875
- Yeah, why were you
in there anyway?

09:44.959 --> 09:48.170
- I had to get something back

09:48.254 --> 09:49.672
that she took from me.

09:49.755 --> 09:51.048
- Could you be more specific?

09:51.132 --> 09:53.801
- It's...

09:53.884 --> 09:54.635
a book.

09:55.761 --> 09:58.347
- That's...that's...

09:58.431 --> 09:58.848
- Totally believable?

09:58.931 --> 10:01.392
- No.

10:01.475 --> 10:02.768
Totally unbelievable,
actually.

10:04.020 --> 10:06.856
Sorry, Emma, you're just
not making any sense.

10:06.939 --> 10:08.357
- I know.

10:08.441 --> 10:09.775
It's like when you're watching
one of those cop shows,

10:09.859 --> 10:11.527
and there's a bunch of twists
and turns in the case,

10:11.610 --> 10:12.737
and you go to the bathroom,

10:12.820 --> 10:14.196
and when you come back,
you're all lost.

10:14.280 --> 10:15.197
- Because you missed
a key piece of information.

10:15.281 --> 10:16.407
- Right.
- So what's the key piece

10:16.490 --> 10:18.784
of information you left out?

10:18.868 --> 10:20.202
- I can't tell you.
- [groans]

10:20.286 --> 10:23.539
- But you have to trust me
that it's for your own good.

10:23.622 --> 10:24.874
- For my own good?

10:24.957 --> 10:26.042
That's like--

10:26.125 --> 10:27.043
[doorknob rattles]

10:27.126 --> 10:28.002
- You have to hide.

10:33.966 --> 10:35.926
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

10:36.010 --> 10:39.764
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:39.847 --> 10:41.390
- Hello there, Emma.

10:41.474 --> 10:43.059
- What are you doing here?

10:43.142 --> 10:46.145
- Making a house call
to the fastest witch in school.

10:46.228 --> 10:47.563
You disappeared.

10:47.646 --> 10:49.523
Didn't even have
to use words.

10:49.607 --> 10:52.777
That's some pretty heavy magic

10:52.860 --> 10:55.654
for someone so young
and inexperienced.

10:56.864 --> 10:58.574
- Yes, well,
I can run very fast.

10:58.657 --> 11:03.245
I suppose some
might call that magical.

11:03.329 --> 11:05.539
- Well,
then it got me thinking.

11:06.499 --> 11:09.377
Perhaps the guardian
was lying.

11:09.460 --> 11:12.171
You are a witch...

11:12.254 --> 11:14.173
and the Chosen One...

11:14.256 --> 11:15.424
<i>[ominous music]</i>

11:15.508 --> 11:20.012
And I will take your powers.

11:20.096 --> 11:20.471
- [sneezes]

11:20.554 --> 11:26.602
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:26.685 --> 11:27.144
[shimmering tone]

11:27.228 --> 11:29.563
[zapping]

11:29.647 --> 11:32.400
<i>[rock music]</i>

11:32.483 --> 11:34.610
[water splashing]

11:34.693 --> 11:36.737
- [grunting]

11:36.821 --> 11:38.489
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:40.032 --> 11:40.616
- Who was that?

11:40.699 --> 11:42.576
Your little friend Andi?

11:42.660 --> 11:45.454
- No, I told you,
no one is here.

11:45.538 --> 11:46.956
- You're good,
and you're fast,

11:47.039 --> 11:50.209
but you can't keep all
your friends safe from me.

11:50.292 --> 11:52.086
You know that, right?

11:52.169 --> 11:53.379
- You don't scare me.

11:53.462 --> 11:55.965
- Your friends are toast.

11:56.048 --> 11:57.007
- Stay away from them.

11:57.091 --> 11:58.634
- Ooh, chilling.

11:58.717 --> 11:59.677
[inhales sharply]

11:59.760 --> 12:00.636
[doorbell rings]

12:00.719 --> 12:01.804
You have a guest.

12:01.887 --> 12:03.514
The drama intensifies.

12:03.597 --> 12:05.850
<i>[ominous music]</i>

12:05.933 --> 12:07.226
- Go away!

12:07.309 --> 12:08.018
We don't want any.

12:08.102 --> 12:09.478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:09.562 --> 12:10.855
TONY: Emma, are you there?
It's me.

12:12.064 --> 12:13.899
- Is that Tony Myers?

12:13.983 --> 12:14.775
- No.

12:14.859 --> 12:16.777
TONY: It's me, Tony Myers.

12:16.861 --> 12:17.695
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:17.778 --> 12:19.071
- Stay away from him.

12:19.155 --> 12:22.491
- Wow, that wasn't
just an act.

12:22.575 --> 12:24.869
You are really protective
of your friends,

12:24.952 --> 12:29.665
and now I know your weak spot,
Emma Alonso.

12:29.748 --> 12:32.334
See you at the eclipse.

12:32.418 --> 12:34.503
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:34.587 --> 12:37.840
TONY: Emma, stand back.

12:37.923 --> 12:39.758
I'm knocking the door down.

12:39.842 --> 12:40.718
Ooh...

12:40.801 --> 12:41.844
[light thudding]

12:41.927 --> 12:43.179
Wow, that's
a really sturdy door.

12:43.262 --> 12:44.346
[chuckles]

12:44.430 --> 12:45.890
Must be made out of oak.

12:45.973 --> 12:48.058
Okay, one more time.

12:48.142 --> 12:50.978
Here I come!

12:51.061 --> 12:53.522
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

12:53.606 --> 12:53.814
- [sighs]

12:55.774 --> 12:57.359
- Can we go back
to Daniel's song?

12:57.443 --> 12:59.195
At least that
had a fun ending.

12:59.278 --> 13:00.362
- No!

13:00.446 --> 13:01.155
I've got to find the perfect

13:01.238 --> 13:02.698
revenge spell for Daniel.

13:04.200 --> 13:05.534
- I finished the laundry.

13:06.785 --> 13:09.705
Oh, wasn't it a relief
that Emma is okay?

13:09.788 --> 13:10.831
Oh, I am going to write

13:10.915 --> 13:13.584
a stern letter
to the school board

13:13.667 --> 13:15.211
about vetting principals
more thoroughly.

13:15.294 --> 13:16.295
Hmm.

13:20.466 --> 13:21.509
Madeline...

13:22.468 --> 13:26.138
It--is that the Hexoren?

13:26.222 --> 13:27.765
- Oh, that's how you say it!

13:27.848 --> 13:29.975
- How could you
keep this from me?

13:30.392 --> 13:32.478
Again?

13:32.561 --> 13:34.396
- Oh, her neck
is turning tomato red.

13:34.480 --> 13:34.939
You know what that means.

13:41.695 --> 13:44.240
- Where did you find that?

13:44.323 --> 13:46.367
- My guardian
gave it to me.

13:46.450 --> 13:48.077
- Your guardian?
I am your guar--

13:48.160 --> 13:50.955
- No,
my real guardian.

13:53.332 --> 13:55.251
[doorbell rings]

14:00.256 --> 14:02.174
- Daniel?

14:04.176 --> 14:05.219
I...

14:05.844 --> 14:07.638
- We need to talk.

14:07.721 --> 14:08.639
- I know.

14:08.722 --> 14:09.932
Come in.
I'll get you a towel.

14:13.435 --> 14:17.147
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

14:17.231 --> 14:20.943
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:21.026 --> 14:21.986
[tea kettle whistles]

14:22.069 --> 14:23.195
- [gasps]

14:23.279 --> 14:24.530
[tea kettle whistling]

14:24.613 --> 14:25.364
- It's just the kettle.

14:25.447 --> 14:27.449
I'm making tea.

14:28.701 --> 14:29.034
- Guess I'm a little
freaked out.

14:33.664 --> 14:34.707
- Here you go.

14:37.501 --> 14:38.002
- Sorry I got
your floors all wet.

14:41.380 --> 14:44.049
- Daniel,
I can explain all this.

14:44.133 --> 14:45.301
- Can you?

14:45.384 --> 14:47.261
Because I was in your house,

14:47.344 --> 14:49.555
and then a second later,
I was in the pool,

14:49.638 --> 14:51.473
and I don't know how--

14:51.557 --> 14:52.850
how to finish this sentence.

14:52.933 --> 14:54.727
- I didn't mean
to send you to the pool,

14:54.810 --> 14:58.689
but I can't seem to master
my transportation spells.

14:58.772 --> 15:01.734
- Your what?
Your spells?

15:01.817 --> 15:03.819
Are you trying to explain
all this away by telling me

15:03.902 --> 15:04.945
you're a witch?

15:06.864 --> 15:08.282
- Yes.

15:08.365 --> 15:09.033
- I can't believe this.

15:09.116 --> 15:10.784
- It's a lot to take in.

15:11.744 --> 15:13.537
Trust me, I know.

15:13.621 --> 15:15.205
- Why didn't you tell me?

15:15.289 --> 15:16.582
- I wanted to tell you,

15:16.665 --> 15:17.374
but I was worried
you'd be all freaked out.

15:17.458 --> 15:18.500
- You think?

15:18.584 --> 15:21.045
<i>[electronic music]</i>

15:23.422 --> 15:24.632
- Daniel, Daniel!
- Whoa.

15:24.715 --> 15:25.007
- Thank goodness
we found you.

15:26.634 --> 15:29.094
- What's going on?

15:29.178 --> 15:30.846
- I have magic powers.

15:32.931 --> 15:35.934
- He must be in shock.
- You too?

15:36.018 --> 15:37.895
- Wait, so you
know about Maddie?

15:38.937 --> 15:39.813
- Maddie?

15:39.897 --> 15:42.524
- Nurse Lily?
- Nurse Lily?

15:42.608 --> 15:44.693
- The principal?
- The principal?

15:44.777 --> 15:45.903
- Oh, must be Emma.

15:45.986 --> 15:47.696
What are the odds
we all guessed wrong?

15:47.780 --> 15:48.697
[all laughing]

15:48.781 --> 15:50.658
- I--I need to sit down.

15:50.741 --> 15:52.534
Okay.

15:52.618 --> 15:54.870
So you're a witch too?

15:54.953 --> 15:55.954
- No, not exactly.

15:56.038 --> 15:58.040
- I know it's a lot
to take in,

15:58.123 --> 16:00.042
so let me recap.

16:00.125 --> 16:02.419
Maddie, the principal,
and Emma are witches.

16:02.503 --> 16:03.712
Diego's a Kanay, and...

16:03.796 --> 16:07.299
Nurse Lily is the witch police?

16:07.383 --> 16:09.218
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah.

16:09.301 --> 16:10.719
- Wait, why are you
telling me this now?

16:10.803 --> 16:13.263
- Tomorrow during the eclipse,
the principal's gonna use me

16:13.347 --> 16:16.183
to steal Maddie's powers,
or maybe Emma's.

16:16.266 --> 16:17.434
We're not exactly sure.

16:17.518 --> 16:18.769
- And when she does that,

16:18.852 --> 16:21.355
Diego's going to turn
into a pile of dust.

16:21.438 --> 16:22.898
- I need some time
to sort through all this...

16:22.981 --> 16:24.316
- Mm-mm.

16:24.400 --> 16:25.567
- So I can come up, you know,
with a rational decision.

16:25.651 --> 16:28.195
- We don't have time
for rational decisions!

16:28.278 --> 16:29.571
- We're on a deadline.

16:29.655 --> 16:30.864
- Okay,
then no questions about it.

16:30.948 --> 16:32.116
We help Emma.
- And Diego.

16:32.199 --> 16:35.202
- Yeah, of course,
and Maddie if she needs it.

16:35.285 --> 16:36.745
- Yeah.
- But we don't tell anyone.

16:36.829 --> 16:39.540
<i>[dramatic musical flourish]</i>

16:41.458 --> 16:44.128
- How can you be painting your
toenails in a time like this?

16:44.211 --> 16:45.629
- It relaxes me.

16:45.713 --> 16:49.633
[breathes deeply]

16:49.717 --> 16:50.926
- Yeah.
[inhales]

16:51.009 --> 16:53.512
Those fumes
are really relaxing.

16:53.595 --> 16:55.889
- Don't you have things
you like to do to calm down?

16:55.973 --> 16:58.100
- Yes, but they all
involve chainsaws,

16:58.183 --> 16:59.935
and you said I couldn't
bring mine anymore

17:00.018 --> 17:01.812
after I accidentally sawed
your chair in half.

17:01.895 --> 17:05.648
<i>[stirring orchestral music]</i>

17:05.733 --> 17:11.780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:11.864 --> 17:13.490
What's this?

17:13.574 --> 17:16.743
Did you get nail polish
on the back of your foot?

17:16.827 --> 17:19.038
- What?
I don't think so.

17:19.121 --> 17:26.462
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:26.545 --> 17:27.963
It's...

17:28.714 --> 17:32.468
A star-shaped birthmark.

17:32.551 --> 17:34.261
- You found it!
You found it!

17:34.344 --> 17:35.471
You're the Chosen One!

17:35.554 --> 17:37.473
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

17:37.556 --> 17:39.683
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:39.767 --> 17:41.977
- I'm here for my daily
Chosen One check-in.

17:42.060 --> 17:44.813
- You are not
the Chosen One.

17:44.897 --> 17:45.814
- What?

17:45.898 --> 17:47.649
Of course
I'm the Chosen One.

17:47.733 --> 17:49.067
- No, you're not.

17:49.151 --> 17:50.652
That horrible guardian
Nurse Lily

17:50.736 --> 17:52.863
made me think you were.

17:52.946 --> 17:54.531
Oh, don't give me that face.

17:54.615 --> 17:56.533
It was an easy mistake
to make.

17:56.617 --> 17:57.785
You did break Emma's spell.

17:57.868 --> 18:00.120
That's hard to do.

18:00.204 --> 18:02.164
I could use a minion
like you.

18:02.247 --> 18:03.332
- [scoffs]
I'm not a minion.

18:03.415 --> 18:05.834
I'm minion master
and the Chosen One.

18:05.918 --> 18:08.170
You said so yourself.

18:08.253 --> 18:10.339
- Relax.
You should be grateful.

18:10.422 --> 18:13.884
Now you won't have
your powers stolen...

18:13.967 --> 18:14.968
by me...

18:15.928 --> 18:17.179
and possibly disappear

18:17.262 --> 18:18.722
into a puddle of goo.

18:18.806 --> 18:20.557
- Wait, that was
your plan all along?

18:20.641 --> 18:23.227
You tricked me?

18:23.310 --> 18:25.062
- I am a witch, aren't I?

18:25.145 --> 18:26.522
[laughs]

18:26.605 --> 18:30.150
- So is Emma the Chosen One?

18:30.234 --> 18:33.195
- She is, for now.

18:33.278 --> 18:36.782
You're just an ordinary witch
who has two choices:

18:36.865 --> 18:39.701
join me or become a frog.

18:41.453 --> 18:44.248
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

18:44.331 --> 18:45.457
- Any sign of the principal
back there?

18:45.541 --> 18:47.543
- Nope.

18:47.626 --> 18:49.419
- What about Daniel?
See him anywhere?

18:49.503 --> 18:50.379
- Seriously?

18:50.462 --> 18:51.839
With everything that's going on,

18:51.922 --> 18:53.090
the eclipse being tonight
and all,

18:53.173 --> 18:54.508
you're asking about Daniel?

18:54.591 --> 18:56.718
- Well, he's a part of it
now that he knows,

18:56.802 --> 18:59.221
and if the principal
finds out he knows, she might,

18:59.304 --> 19:02.224
you know, frogger-ize him.

19:02.307 --> 19:04.476
- Well, that would
make him swim faster.

19:04.560 --> 19:07.354
- We look ridiculous.
- Hey.

19:07.437 --> 19:08.772
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:08.856 --> 19:11.400
You were supposed
to be covering left flank.

19:11.483 --> 19:13.610
- I was.
She came up on the right flank.

19:13.694 --> 19:16.238
- Oh, this is going
to be way too easy.

19:16.321 --> 19:17.447
- No, it's not,

19:17.531 --> 19:21.410
because there's
more than just the two of us.

19:21.493 --> 19:22.369
We've got a whole posse.

19:22.452 --> 19:25.372
- Who?
Your math geek father?

19:25.455 --> 19:29.751
That doggy-paddling,
unibrow-ridden Daniel?

19:29.835 --> 19:32.337
The mumbling magician Tony?

19:32.421 --> 19:33.797
- Yeah.

19:33.881 --> 19:35.632
Yeah, and don't even think
about turning them into frogs.

19:35.716 --> 19:38.093
- Oh, I won't.

19:38.176 --> 19:41.096
I'll turn them into flies
to feed to my frogs,

19:41.179 --> 19:43.182
and I think
I'll start with you.

19:43.265 --> 19:45.934
- You'll have
to go through me!

19:46.018 --> 19:49.938
- Oh, don't worry,
I will, but not yet.

19:50.022 --> 19:53.150
I need to keep
the bait fresh.

19:53.233 --> 19:55.652
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:55.736 --> 19:56.653
- What now?

19:56.737 --> 19:59.072
- We need help.

19:59.156 --> 19:59.865
We have to ask
you-know-who for help.

19:59.948 --> 20:02.993
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:03.076 --> 20:03.535
[knock on door]

20:03.619 --> 20:05.495
- Come in.

20:05.579 --> 20:07.289
[door clicks open]

20:07.372 --> 20:08.749
- Maddie.

20:08.832 --> 20:10.834
- You?
Get out!

20:10.918 --> 20:12.211
- Can I just talk to you
for a minute?

20:12.294 --> 20:14.046
- 30 seconds.

20:14.129 --> 20:16.506
- Look,
you're not the Chosen One.

20:16.590 --> 20:17.674
I am,
and you should be thankful,

20:17.758 --> 20:19.801
because the principal--
- I already know that!

20:19.885 --> 20:21.303
Did you come in here
to rub it in my face?

20:21.386 --> 20:22.846
- No, of course not!

20:22.930 --> 20:24.973
It's just, the principal is
planning to steal my powers

20:25.057 --> 20:27.309
and hurt Diego in the process,
and Daniel thinks that--

20:27.392 --> 20:28.185
- Daniel?

20:28.268 --> 20:30.604
- Yeah,
Daniel knows everything.

20:32.064 --> 20:33.982
- Why are you even here again?

20:34.066 --> 20:35.150
I have a dance
to get ready for.

20:35.233 --> 20:36.151
- We need your help.
- Why would I help you?

20:36.234 --> 20:38.403
I'm not involved in any of this.

20:38.487 --> 20:41.657
- It does involve you.
It involves everyone.

20:41.740 --> 20:43.075
If the principal
takes my powers,

20:43.158 --> 20:46.370
who knows what she'll do
to our friends, our families.

20:52.417 --> 20:54.753
- What's in it for me?

20:54.836 --> 20:57.297
- Besides making sure evil
doesn't take over the universe?

20:57.381 --> 20:57.422
- Yeah.

20:59.675 --> 21:00.676
What about your shoes?

21:00.759 --> 21:03.512
- Okay, sure,
you can have my shoes.

21:05.013 --> 21:07.432
Oh, you mean right now?

21:07.516 --> 21:09.267
<i>[hip-hop music]</i>

21:09.351 --> 21:10.352
[sighs]

21:10.435 --> 21:12.187
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:12.270 --> 21:15.148
There, they're all yours.

21:15.232 --> 21:16.316
- Oh, and one other thing.

21:16.733 --> 21:18.902
Daniel.

21:18.986 --> 21:20.278
- What?
No way, forget it.

21:20.362 --> 21:21.863
- Then forget
me helping you.

21:21.947 --> 21:23.699
- Wait, but come on, Maddie.

21:23.782 --> 21:25.951
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:26.034 --> 21:28.704
Um, can I at least have my
shoes back so I can walk home?

21:28.787 --> 21:30.539
- No!

21:31.748 --> 21:32.791
[banging noise]

21:33.709 --> 21:36.044
- Hex?

21:42.092 --> 21:46.388
<i>[tense music]</i>

21:46.471 --> 21:48.098
Is it you, Hex?

21:48.181 --> 21:49.433
- No, it's me.

21:49.516 --> 21:50.308
- [screams]

21:55.772 --> 21:56.815
Daniel, I--

21:56.898 --> 21:59.860
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

21:59.943 --> 22:01.903
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:03.321 --> 22:06.324
{\an8}<i>[upbeat pop music]</i>

22:06.408 --> 22:13.415
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>
